# Build-context hygiene for the KAINE image (design §7).
#
# NOTHING sensitive or heavyweight enters the build context. The image ships
# ONLY the committed all-off config/kaine.toml (copied explicitly in the
# Dockerfile); operator overlays, secrets, voices, adapters, and all entity
# state are mounted at runtime, never built in. Model weights live in the
# kaine-models volume, never a layer. Podman reads .containerignore, which is a
# copy of this file.

# --- Entity state (never in an image; owner-only, encrypted at rest) ---
state/
runtime-logs/
backups/
research_out/

# --- Operator config + secrets (bind-mounted read-only at runtime, never COPYed) ---
config/*.operator.toml
config/secrets.toml
compose/.env
.env

# --- Private voices + adapters ---
voices/
**/*.wav
**/*.flac
state/hypnos/adapters/
state/forks/merged_adapters/

# --- Model weights / caches (provisioned to the kaine-models volume) ---
models/
**/*.gguf
**/*.safetensors
**/*.ckpt
**/*.pt
**/*.bin
.cache/
**/__pycache__/
*.py[cod]

# --- Dev / venv / VCS / editor noise ---
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/
.git/
.github/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.DS_Store

# --- Docs / tests / research artifacts not needed at runtime ---
tests/
docs/
openspec/
eval_probes/
data/
